<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-506-918  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 506 918.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Government Computer News  May 28 1990 v9 n11 p40(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Chipcom links isolated LANs. (Chipcom Corp.'s LAN-to-LAN) (productannouncement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Olsen, Florence.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Chipcom Corp. (products).andO;Product:   Chipcom LAN-to-LAN (Communications board) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionCommunications Boards-CardsFiber OpticsEthernetLocal Area Networks.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Chipcom Links Isolated LANsandM;Chipcom Corp. has a new $1,095 communications board that connects isolatedfiber Ethernet local area networks.andM;Pilot installations of fiber-optic networks using related Chipcom componentsare in scattered locations throughout the federal government, Chipcomspokesman Dennis Kroger said.andM;The Waltham, Mass., networking company designed the LAN-to-LAN fiber Ethernetboard to run in the open-platform multiport repeater made by 3Com Corp.,andO;Santa Clara, Calif.andP;  Sites that use 3Com's MultiConnect Repeater equipmentcan use the new Chipcom fiber Ethernet boards to extend existing fiber-opticLANs to form a backbone fiber network.andM;&quot;What we have done is integrate our ORnet capability with 3Com's MultiConnectcapability,&quot; said Kroger, manager of federal sales for Chipcom.andM;The LAN-to-LAN fiber network component uses Chipcom's ORnet &quot;repeaterlesstechnology,&quot; which lets organizations build extensive fiber backbone networksby linking many multiport repeaters.andM;&quot;What we would recommend is putting one of our fiber star couplers on thefirst floor of the building and then running a fiber cable to each of thefiber modules in the hub,&quot; said Frnak Fuller, Chipcom's fiber-optic productmanager.andM;The LAN-to-LAN fiber Ethernet board has two ports, so if one link fails, theother link will take over and keep the backbone up.andM;It is wired the same way the Fiber Distributed Data Interface (FDDI) will bewired, Kroger said.andM;&quot;If you were to put this module in a LAN configuration now, you could migrateto FDDI in the future without any change in your cabling plan,&quot; he said.andM;Contact Chipcom federal sales manager Dennis Kroger, tel.andP;  703-391-2710.andO;</TEXT></DOC>